headline: One Agriculture Equipment Giant Dominated Last Month Despite Sector Challenges
summary: The U.S. economy added just 50,000 jobs in December, marking the slowest labor market expansion in years and pushing unemployment to 4.4%. This cooling signals potential Federal Reserve flexibility on rates, creating a critical backdrop for capital-intensive industries like farm equipment.
